title: Area Roundup: Minooka girls place third at IESA cross country meet
text:
Area Roundup: Minooka girls place third at IESA cross country meet Published: Monday, Oct. 19, 2015 9:33 p.m. CDT By: STAFF REPORTS 
NORMAL – The Minooka Junior High girls finished third in the IESA state cross country meet Saturday. 
It was the first trophy for the Indians since 1981, when they also took third place. Eighth-grader Madalynn Olenick ran the 2-mile course at Maxwell Park in 11:50 for a 21st individual place that earned her all-state honors. Eighth-grader Taryn Sandei (12:10) took 31st place, followed by eighth-grader Olivia Kics (12:11, 32nd), fifth-grader Gabriela Kics (12:12, 34th), seventh-grader Morgan Tomaselli (12:28, 46th), seventh-grader Kaylee Ratcliff (12:57, 96th) and eighth-grader Abbey Rivera (13:00, 113th). 
The Minooka boys had two individuals in the race, as eighth-grader Hector Ramos took 40th with a time of 11:04 and classmate Jared Bieker finished in 11:14, good for 59th place. 
GIRLS SWIMMING 
NIB 12 Invite: The Morris team took fifth place at the NIB 12 Conference Invite in Sterling. Top place winners were Meghan Carr and Madi Zurawski. Carr took third in diving on the varsity and Zurawski won the JV Division. Alex Kaste took fifth in the 100 breaststroke with a time of 1:22.47.
